      {
        "id": 2823730,
        "name": "Dale McClaran",
        "username": "Dale_McClaran",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dale_mcclaran/{size}/683_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-25T17:01:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>2017 Domaine Martelet de Cherisey Meursault-Blagny 1er Cru La Genelotte - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault-Blagny 1er Cru (2/25/2020)<br>\nWith a generally forwarding leaning vintage of 2017 and richness of good Meursault, I was still taken aback at how incredibly seductive this was. A well defined note of ripe yellow peach plays well notes oatmeal and hazelnuts. Acidity? no problem, lemony citrus skins constantly keep this beauty moving along at just the right tempo. The coverage impresses in the mouth, the finish is clean, and no chance my 2nd bottle is going to last long as I\u2019m already thinking about opening it soon. Marvelous. (94 points)</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
